<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Use of percentage as basis stepwise populating our forecast timeseries forward</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">simulate_arrivals_pct</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">listrandmultipler</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">total</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">simulation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">rand</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">listrandmultipler</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">projection</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">total</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="n">rand</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">100</span>
        <span class="n">simulation</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">projection</span><span class="p">))</span>
        <span class="n">total</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">projection</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">simulation</span>

<span class="c1"># Use of absolute figures as basis stepwise populating our forecast timeseries forward</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">simulate_arrivals_abs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">listrandpassenger</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">total</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">simulation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">rand</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">listrandpassenger</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">projection</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">total</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">rand</span>
        <span class="n">simulation</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">projection</span><span class="p">))</span>
        <span class="n">total</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">projection</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">simulation</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<ul>
<li>Based on the sample parameters from the past observations of monthly passenger arrivals, we make some simple assumptions about the set of all possible future growth scenarios </li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Sample-our-growth-inputs-from-a-normal-distribution">Sample our growth inputs from a <em>normal</em> distribution<a class="anchor-link" href="#Sample-our-growth-inputs-from-a-normal-distribution">¶</a></h2><ul>
<li>With the parameters mean = 3993 and Std Dev = 87934 from our sample population above</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [9]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Reset our data</span>
<span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">collectlistOfRuns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">collectlistOfNumbers</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">countbelow</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
<span class="c1"># For reproducibility</span>
<span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">seed</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">seed</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">n</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">noofruns</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">listOfNumbers</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="c1"># Get random growth figures from specified distribution</span>
    <span class="c1"># Add dates to forecast ahead</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">x</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">mthrange</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">generatednumber</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">normalvariate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">3993</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">87934</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">listOfNumbers</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">generatednumber</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">collectlistOfNumbers</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">generatednumber</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="c1"># Do the monte Carlo here</span>
    <span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">simulate_arrivals_abs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'no_of_air_passenger_arrivals'</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">iloc</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">listOfNumbers</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="c1"># Check if the end of MC sim is below our projected figures</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o"><=</span> <span class="n">y2</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]:</span>
        <span class="n">countbelow</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
    <span class="c1"># Collect Data to be plotted later</span>
    <span class="n">collectlistOfRuns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]))</span>

<span class="c1">#Plot our results</span>
<span class="n">plotexpdata</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">mthrange</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">noofruns</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfRuns</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfNumbers</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">countbelow</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">pct</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Lower bound of our forcasted passengers/mth at </span><span class="si">%s</span><span class="s2"> is </span><span class="si">%.4f</span><span class="s2"> mil"</span> <span class="o">%</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">date_end</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">min</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">1000000</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Upper bound of our forcasted passengers/mth at </span><span class="si">%s</span><span class="s2"> is </span><span class="si">%.4f</span><span class="s2"> mil"</span> <span class="o">%</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">date_end</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">max</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">1000000</span><span class="p">))</span>

<h2 id="Sample-our-growth-inputs-from-a-triangular-distribution">Sample our growth inputs from a <em>triangular</em> distribution<a class="anchor-link" href="#Sample-our-growth-inputs-from-a-triangular-distribution">¶</a></h2><ul>
<li>Observation from the normal disribution of abs growths rates above , we use upper/lower bound of +-200k with center 3993 as parameters for our triangular dist</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [11]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Reset our data</span>
<span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">collectlistOfRuns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">collectlistOfNumbers</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">countbelow</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
<span class="c1"># For reproducibility</span>
<span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">seed</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">seed</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">n</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">noofruns</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">listOfNumbers</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="c1"># Get random growth figures from specified distribution</span>
    <span class="c1"># Add dates to forecast ahead</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">x</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">mthrange</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">generatednumber</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">triangular</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">200000</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">200000</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">3993</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">listOfNumbers</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">generatednumber</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">collectlistOfNumbers</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">generatednumber</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="c1"># Do the monte Carlo here</span>
    <span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">simulate_arrivals_abs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'no_of_air_passenger_arrivals'</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">iloc</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">listOfNumbers</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="c1"># Check if the end of MC sim is below our projected figures</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o"><=</span> <span class="n">y2</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]:</span>
        <span class="n">countbelow</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
    <span class="c1"># Collect Data to be plotted later</span>
    <span class="n">collectlistOfRuns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]))</span>

<span class="c1">#Plot our results</span>
<span class="n">plotexpdata</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">mthrange</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">noofruns</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfRuns</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfNumbers</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">countbelow</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">pct</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Upper bound of our forcasted passengers/mth at </span><span class="si">%s</span><span class="s2"> is </span><span class="si">%.4f</span><span class="s2"> mil"</span> <span class="o">%</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">date_end</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">max</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mi">1000000</span><span class="p">))</span>

<h2 id="Sample-our-growth-inputs-from-a-uniform-distribution">Sample our growth inputs from a <em>uniform</em> distribution<a class="anchor-link" href="#Sample-our-growth-inputs-from-a-uniform-distribution">¶</a></h2><ul>
<li>Using similar +- 200k as parameters for our uniform distribution</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [13]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Reset our data</span>
<span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">collectlistOfRuns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">collectlistOfNumbers</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">countbelow</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
<span class="c1"># For reproducibility</span>
<span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">seed</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">seed</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">n</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">noofruns</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">listOfNumbers</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="c1"># Get random growth figures from specified distribution</span>
    <span class="c1"># Add dates to forecast ahead</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">x</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">mthrange</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">generatednumber</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">uniform</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">200000</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">200000</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">listOfNumbers</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">generatednumber</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">collectlistOfNumbers</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">generatednumber</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="c1"># Do the monte Carlo here</span>
    <span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">simulate_arrivals_abs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'no_of_air_passenger_arrivals'</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">iloc</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">listOfNumbers</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="c1"># Check if the end of MC sim is below our projected figures</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o"><=</span> <span class="n">y2</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]:</span>
        <span class="n">countbelow</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>
    <span class="c1"># Collect Data to be plotted later</span>
    <span class="n">collectlistOfRuns</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">listOfForcast</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]))</span>

<span class="c1">#Plot our results</span>
<span class="n">plotexpdata</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">mthrange</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">noofruns</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfForcast</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfRuns</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">collectlistOfNumbers</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">countbelow</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">pct</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<h1 id="Prophet:-Automatic-Forecasting-Procedure">Prophet: Automatic Forecasting Procedure<a class="anchor-link" href="#Prophet:-Automatic-Forecasting-Procedure">¶</a></h1><p>Prophet is a procedure for forecasting time series data.  It is based on an additive model where non-linear trends are fit with yearly and weekly seasonality, plus holidays.  It works best with daily periodicity data with at least one year of historical data.  Prophet is robust to missing data, shifts in the trend, and large outliers.</p>
<p>Prophet is open source software released by Facebook's Core Data Science team.</p>
<p>Full documentation and examples available at the homepage:</p>
<p><a href="https://facebookincubator.github.io/prophet/">https://facebookincubator.github.io/prophet/</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [15]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">fbprophet</span> <span class="k">import</span> <span class="n">Prophet</span>

<span class="n">fbtest</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pulldatagov</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">datauid</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1"># Format to Prophet's inputs ds , y</span>
<span class="n">fbtest</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">rename</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">columns</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">{</span><span class="s2">"month"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"ds"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"no_of_air_passenger_arrivals"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"y"</span><span class="p">},</span><span class="n">inplace</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">fbtest</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">head</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">m</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Prophet</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">yearly_seasonality</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">weekly_seasonality</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Make Monthly Forcast</span>

<span class="n">future</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">make_future_dataframe</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">periods</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">mthrange</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">freq</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'M'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">forecast</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">future</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">forecast</span><span class="p">[[</span><span class="s1">'ds'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'yhat'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'yhat_lower'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'yhat_upper'</span><span class="p">]]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tail</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<hr>
<h1 id="Notes">Notes<a class="anchor-link" href="#Notes">¶</a></h1><ol>
<li>Looking at the monte carlo results of course it does not make sense for the no. of arrival passengers to be negative, below zero. On a side note, data on departure passengers is tracked separately by the Civil Aviation Authority of Singapore. </li>
<li>Passenger arrivals are  a function of air vehicle and terminal capacity as well as airport attractiveness / connectivity, this is not explored in this experiment.</li>
<li>From the various shapes of the random distributions in our monte carlo exercises above, it shown that the polynomial projections of historial data tend to over-estimate the future, the spread of predictions of all simulations are similar.</li>
<li>As a comparision, Facebooks' Prophet predicts Changi's Arrival Passengers in the range of <strong> 4-5 million </strong> per mth in year 2035 based on past observations.</li>
<li>The tighter confidence interval range for Prophet's forecast indicates algorithm has more certainty than running monte carlo simulations.</li>
<li>Check any interesting trends in the log transformation of passengers arrivals.</li>
</ol>
</hr></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [22]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Do Log transform</span>
<span class="n">df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pulldatagov</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">datauid</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'no_of_air_passenger_arrivals'</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'no_of_air_passenger_arrivals'</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">mdates</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date2num</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">as_matrix</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">'month'</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">flatten</span><span class="p">())</span>
<span class="n">y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">df</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">as_matrix</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">'no_of_air_passenger_arrivals'</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">flatten</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">z</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">polyfit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">y</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">p</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">poly1d</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">z</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">x2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">mdates</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date2num</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">date_end</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">y2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">p</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x2</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">fig</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">figure</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fig</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add_subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">221</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="s2">"Year"</span><span class="p">),</span><span class="n">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">16</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="s2">"Log of Passenger Arrivals"</span><span class="p">),</span><span class="n">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">16</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot_date</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'month'</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'no_of_air_passenger_arrivals'</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">fmt</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'-'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x2</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">y2</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'r--'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">'Actual'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'Trend'</span> <span class="p">],</span><span class="n">loc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'upper left'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">12</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">show</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

/* CSS font colors for translated ANSI colors. */

div.cell {
  /* Old browsers */
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-box-align: stretch;
  display: -moz-box;
  -moz-box-orient: vertical;
  -moz-box-align: stretch;
  display: box;
  box-orient: vertical;
  box-align: stretch;
  /* Modern browsers */
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: stretch;
  border-radius: 2px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  -moz-box-sizing: border-box;
  -webkit-box-sizing: border-box;
  border-width: 1px;
  border-style: solid;
  border-color: transparent;
  width: 100%;
  padding: 5px;
  /* This acts as a spacer between cells, that is outside the border */
  margin: 0px;
  outline: none;
  border-left-width: 1px;
  padding-left: 5px;
  background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent -40px, transparent 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 100%);
}
div.cell.jupyter-soft-selected {
  border-left-color: #90CAF9;
  border-left-color: #E3F2FD;
  border-left-width: 1px;
  padding-left: 5px;
  border-right-color: #E3F2FD;
  border-right-width: 1px;
  background: #E3F2FD;
}
@media print {
  div.cell.jupyter-soft-selected {
    border-color: transparent;
  }
}
div.cell.selected {
  border-color: #ababab;
  border-left-width: 0px;
  padding-left: 6px;
  background: linear-gradient(to right, #42A5F5 -40px, #42A5F5 5px, transparent 5px, transparent 100%);
}
@media print {
  div.cell.selected {
    border-color: transparent;
  }
}
div.cell.selected.jupyter-soft-selected {
  border-left-width: 0;
  padding-left: 6px;
  background: linear-gradient(to right, #42A5F5 -40px, #42A5F5 7px, #E3F2FD 7px, #E3F2FD 100%);
}
.edit_mode div.cell.selected {
  border-color: #66BB6A;
  border-left-width: 0px;
  padding-left: 6px;
  background: linear-gradient(to right, #66BB6A -40px, #66BB6A 5px, transparent 5px, transparent 100%);
}
@media print {
  .edit_mode div.cell.selected {
    border-color: transparent;
  }
}
.prompt {
  /* This needs to be wide enough for 3 digit prompt numbers: In[100]: */
  min-width: 14ex;
  /* This padding is tuned to match the padding on the CodeMirror editor. */
  padding: 0.4em;
  margin: 0px;
  font-family: monospace;
  text-align: right;
  /* This has to match that of the the CodeMirror class line-height below */
  line-height: 1.21429em;
  /* Don't highlight prompt number selection */
  -webkit-touch-callout: none;
  -webkit-user-select: none;
  -khtml-user-select: none;
  -moz-user-select: none;
  -ms-user-select: none;
  user-select: none;
  /* Use default cursor */
  cursor: default;
}
@media (max-width: 540px) {
  .prompt {
    text-align: left;
  }
}
div.inner_cell {
  /* Old browsers */
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-box-align: stretch;
  display: -moz-box;
  -moz-box-orient: vertical;
  -moz-box-align: stretch;
  display: box;
  box-orient: vertical;
  box-align: stretch;
  /* Modern browsers */
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: stretch;
  /* Old browsers */
  -webkit-box-flex: 1;
  -moz-box-flex: 1;
  box-flex: 1;
  /* Modern browsers */
  flex: 1;
}
@-moz-document url-prefix() {
  div.inner_cell {
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

/* input_area and input_prompt must match in top border and margin for alignment */
div.input_area {

  border-radius: 2px;

}
/* This is needed so that empty prompt areas can collapse to zero height when there
   is no content in the output_subarea and the prompt. The main purpose of this is

div.prompt:empty {
  padding-top: 0;

}

}
div.unrecognized_cell .inner_cell {

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Where-do-people-hangout-at-Changi-Airport?">Where do people hangout at Changi Airport?<a class="anchor-link" href="#Where-do-people-hangout-at-Changi-Airport?">¶</a></h2><p><img alt="Changi Airport" src="https://wykeith.github.io/images/changi-layout.jpg" /></p>
<ol>
<li>Since I'm putting together a generic benchmarking tool for the evaluation of a development project at work ...</li>
<li>A buddy of mine does research work in retail sector esp for airports, so lets see if I can adapt this tool for the airport retail industry.</li>
<li>Thus the research question above , lets see if we can derive some interesting insights!</li>
<li>In the context of planning and urban design , through the analysis of space use patterns I hope to share some (retail) planning principles.</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Fetch-Foursquare-location-links">Fetch Foursquare location links<a class="anchor-link" href="#Fetch-Foursquare-location-links">¶</a></h3><ol>
<li>Starting at Changi Airport as seed venue</li>
<li>Fetching the 5 next venues</li>
<li>For each of the 5 venues fetch the 5 next venues</li>
<li>Repeat until saturation (no new locations)</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [2]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># bbox = [103.6182, 1.1158, 104.4085, 1.4706] # Bounding box for Singapore</span>
<span class="n">bbox</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mf">103.975796</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">1.341720</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">104.000917</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">1.365318</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="c1"># Bounding box for Changi Airport Terminals</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [3]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">new_crawl</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span> <span class="c1"># list of locations to be crawled</span>
<span class="n">done</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span> <span class="c1"># list of crawled locations</span>
<span class="n">links</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span> <span class="c1"># list of tuples that represent links between locations</span>
<span class="n">venues</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">DataFrame</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="c1"># dictionary of locations id => meta-data on location</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Set seed values for Changi Airport and T1,T2,T3
Depth is the number of recursive crawling processes.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [73]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">#,"4b0bd124f964a520e03323e3" : Changi Airport</span>
<span class="c1">#,"4b1baa6bf964a52087fc23e3" : Terminal 1</span>
<span class="c1">#,"4b1b9ec2f964a52041fc23e3" : Terminal 2</span>
<span class="c1">#,"4b1baa07f964a52084fc23e3" : Terminal 3</span>

<span class="n">to_crawl</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"4b0bd124f964a520e03323e3"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"4b1baa6bf964a52087fc23e3"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"4b1b9ec2f964a52041fc23e3"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"4b1baa07f964a52084fc23e3"</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">depth</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">8</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [5]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">depth</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">new_crawl</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Step "</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="s2">": "</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">venues</span><span class="p">))</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="s2">" locations and "</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">links</span><span class="p">))</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="s2">" links. "</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">to_crawl</span><span class="p">))</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="s2">" venues to go."</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">to_crawl</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">v</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">venues</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">res</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">client</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">venues</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">v</span><span class="p">)</span>
            <span class="n">venues</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">venues</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">DataFrame</span><span class="p">({</span><span class="s2">"name"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"venue"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"name"</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="s2">"users"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">res</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"venue"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"stats"</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s2">"usersCount"</span><span class="p">],</span>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>PageRank has been used to rank spaces or streets to predict how many people (pedestrians or vehicles) come to the individual spaces or streets. The networks of urban spaces in London, for instance, have up to 20,000 nodes and 100,000 links. In these networks, weighted PageRank best predicts human mobility in a case study of movement within London. Individuals and businesses are likely to colocate in places with high connectivity.</p>
</div>
</div>

<span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">fig</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add_subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">111</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">venues</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">by</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'pagerank'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">inplace</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">)</span>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Betweenness centrality finds wide application in network theory: it represents the degree of which nodes stand between each other. For example, in a telecommunications network, a node with higher betweenness centrality would have more control over the network, because more information will pass through that node. Betweenness centrality was devised as a general measure of centrality it applies to a wide range of problems in network theory, including problems related to social networks, biology, transport and scientific cooperation.</p>

<h2 id="Notes:">Notes:<a class="anchor-link" href="#Notes:">¶</a></h2><ol>
<li>Looks like people love drinking coffee and smoking at our airports</li>
<li>Butterfly garden is more popular than sunflower garden! (I personally like sunflowers) </li>
<li>Besides food & beverages, spending time shopping at DFS is important according to pagerank</li>
<li>Fastfood joints are good common meeting spaces were most people traffic will intersect, as observed from the network graph above. When planning spaces , put them in the center of floor plans as they are also key people magnets (people attract people!)</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">numpy</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">np</span>

<span class="n">pivot</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pivot_table</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">venues</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">venues</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'cat'</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isin</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filterlist</span><span class="p">)],</span> <span class="n">values</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'users'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">columns</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'cat'</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">aggfunc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_frame</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">figure</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">16</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="c1"># plot chart</span>
<span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">121</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">aspect</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'equal'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">pivot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sort_values</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">by</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'users'</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">:]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">kind</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'pie'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'users'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">ax</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">autopct</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="si">%1.1f%%</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="p">,</span> 
 <span class="n">startangle</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">90</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">shadow</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">legend</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">14</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Top 20 Retail Mix by Users'</span><span class="p">)</span>

}

}
div.cell {
  /* Old browsers */
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-box-align: stretch;
  display: -moz-box;

  display: box;

  box-align: stretch;
  /* Modern browsers */
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: stretch;
  border-radius: 2px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  -moz-box-sizing: border-box;
  -webkit-box-sizing: border-box;
  border-width: 1px;
  border-style: solid;
  border-color: transparent;
  width: 100%;
  padding: 5px;
  /* This acts as a spacer between cells, that is outside the border */
  margin: 0px;
  outline: none;
  border-left-width: 1px;
  padding-left: 5px;
  background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent -40px, transparent 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 100%);
}

  border-left-color: #90CAF9;
  border-left-color: #E3F2FD;

  border-right-color: #E3F2FD;

}

    border-color: transparent;
  }
}
div.cell.selected {
  border-color: #ababab;

}
@media print {
  div.cell.selected {
    border-color: transparent;
  }
}
div.cell.selected.jupyter-soft-selected {
  border-left-width: 0;

}
.edit_mode div.cell.selected {
  border-color: #66BB6A;

}

    border-color: transparent;
  }
}
.prompt {
  /* This needs to be wide enough for 3 digit prompt numbers: In[100]: */
  min-width: 14ex;
  /* This padding is tuned to match the padding on the CodeMirror editor. */
  padding: 0.4em;
  margin: 0px;
  font-family: monospace;
  text-align: right;

  line-height: 1.21429em;
  /* Don't highlight prompt number selection */
  -webkit-touch-callout: none;
  -webkit-user-select: none;
  -khtml-user-select: none;
  -moz-user-select: none;
  -ms-user-select: none;

  cursor: default;

    text-align: left;
  }
}
div.inner_cell {

  display: -webkit-box;

<h3 id="Budget-2017">Budget 2017<a class="anchor-link" href="#Budget-2017">¶</a></h3><p><a href="http://www.singaporebudget.gov.sg"><img alt="Logo" src="https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-eKS7dGaZofs/VvffxrZhdYI/AAAAAAAAln8/kFVr5q-LdkE-eG8H9VKkpaN_voiuU1ZFQ/s400/Singapore-Budget-2016-where-the-money-going-ST-photo.jpg" /></a></p>
<ol>
<li>It is the time of the year again in Feb, when the Government will announce the balance of projected revenues against expenditures for the upcoming Financial Year 2017.</li>
<li>One can get the Budget report from offical sources such as the budget <a href="http://www.singaporebudget.gov.sg">website</a> or from the usual mainstream media outlets</li>
<li>Lets pull some data from last's year budget programmatically for our visualisation</li>
<li>Personally 2017 is a tough year for me as I'm juggling Financial and Family commitments in the face of employment uncertainity</li>
<li>Lets see what the Government will unveil come 20 Feb 2017 , will it be a surplus or deficit</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [1]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="o">%</span><span class="k">matplotlib</span> inline

<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">urllib.request</span> <span class="k">import</span> <span class="n">Request</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">urlopen</span> 
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">numpy</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">np</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [2]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Trick webserver into giving us the xls rather than a 403</span>
<span class="n">headers</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="s1">'User-Agent'</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s1">'Mozilla/5.0'</span> <span class="p">}</span>
<span class="n">budget2016url</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'http://www.singaporebudget.gov.sg/data/budget_2016/download/FY2016_Analysis_of_Revenue_and_Expenditure.xls'</span>
<span class="n">filename</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"FY2016_Analysis_of_Revenue_and_Expenditure.xls"</span>

<h2 id="Back-from-a-Hiatus">Back from a Hiatus<a class="anchor-link" href="#Back-from-a-Hiatus">¶</a></h2><p><img alt="Zero results: 'snake charming' and 'haberdashery'.  (Things like 'car' and 'boating' and such are of course the highest, by a huge margin" src="https://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/dangers.png" title="Zero results: 'snake charming' and 'haberdashery'.  (Things like 'car' and 'boating' and such are of course the highest, by a huge margin" /></p>
<ol>
<li>It has been someime since I've been penning down my thoughts online through formal channels</li>
<li>Due to many factors from work and family</li>
<li>I caught up with my high school buddy of 20yrs recently</li>
<li>He had suggested I start a blog about my experiments & explorations</li>
<li><p>After giving much thought and internal struggle, I decided the benefits would still outweight the downsides of blogging down my thoughts. Such as</p>
<ul>
<li>Establishing online presence</li>
<li>Offload my overtaxed braincells</li>
<li>Sharpen programming & writing skills</li>
<li>Solicit different perspectives</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Now to find a way to implement feedback/comments on static github pages</p>
<p>Suggestions are <a href="mailto:wykeith+blog@gmail.com">Welcome</a> !</p>
